    <div class="prose fade-in">
      <p>Ronaldo's technique was inseparable from his speed — not diminished by it, but <strong>enhanced</strong>. He didn't just dribble at pace; he dribbled through chaos. His touch was soft at 35 km/h, his balance intact in traffic, his change of direction synchronized with the ball as if he were wired to it.</p>
      <p>Van Basten was geometry turned poetry. Tall, lean, and upright, he moved with a ballet-like fluidity. His shooting technique was impeccable — right foot, left foot, volleys, half-volleys, acrobatic finishes. His coordination made him a natural for overhead kicks and complex gestures. <strong>His famous volley against the USSR at Euro 1988 remains the most technically perfect goal ever scored.</strong></p>
